title: USGS Earthquake Data, world, 1973-2001
name: USGS Earthquake Data, world, 1973-2001
description: This data was collected from USGS through the National Atlas at the following site - http://nationalatlas.gov/mld/quksigx.html.  From the original data set a subset was created of earthquakes from 1973 to 2001 that were over a magnitude of 5.  Also the earthquake activity associated with nuclear testing in Nevada was excluded, so that only natural hazards would be conveyed in the data set. This data set was originally used to look at earthquake risk to commodity flows across highway, rail, and waterways.
